name: Bulbasaur
description: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

name: Ivysaur
description: There is a plant bulb on its back. When it absorbs nutrients, the bulb is said to blossom into a large flower.

name: Venusaur
description: A bewitching aroma wafts from its flower. The fragrance becalms those engaged in a battle.

name: Charmander
description: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

name: Charmeleon
description: It lashes about with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.

name: Charizard
description: Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.

name: Squirtle
description: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

name: Wartortle
description: This Pokémon is very popular as a pet. Its fur-covered tail is a symbol of its longevity.

name: Blastoise
description: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

name: Caterpie
description: Caterpie has a voracious appetite. It can devour leaves bigger than its body right before your eyes. From its antenna, this Pokémon releases a terrifically strong odor.

name: Metapod
description: Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can’t withstand a harsh attack.

name: Butterfree
description: The wings are protected by rain-repellent dust. As a result, this Pokémon can fly about even in rain.

name: Weedle
description: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.

name: Kakuna
description: This Pokémon is in a temporary stage while making its body. It is almost completely unable to move on its own.

name: Beedrill
description: A Beedrill is extremely territorial. For safety reasons, no one should ever approach its nest. If angered, they will attack in a swarm.

name: Pidgey
description: Does not like to fight. It hides in tall grass and so on, foraging for food such as small bugs.

name: Pidgeotto
description: The claws on its feet are well developed. It can carry prey such as an Exeggcute to its nest over 60 miles away.

name: Pidgeot
description: It spreads its gorgeous wings widely to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach-2 speed.

name: Rattata
description: A Rattata is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly moves its ears and listens for danger. It will make its nest anywhere.

name: Raticate
description: A Raticate’s sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.

name: Spearow
description: Its loud cry can be heard over half a mile away. If its high, keening cry is heard echoing all around, it is a sign that they are warning each other of danger.

name: Fearow
description: Its huge and magnificent wings can keep it aloft in the sky. It can remain flying a whole day without landing.

name: Ekans
description: A very common sight in grassland, etc. It flicks its tongue in and out to sense danger in its surroundings.

name: Arbok
description: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.

name: Pikachu
description: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.

name: Raichu
description: Its electric charges can reach even 100,000 volts. Careless contact can cause even an Indian elephant to faint.

name: Sandshrew
description: It burrows and lives underground. If threatened, it curls itself up into a ball for protection.

name: Sandslash
description: It is adept at attacking with the spines on its back and its sharp claws while quickly scurrying about.

name: Nidoran-f
description: Though small, it must be treated with caution because of its powerfully toxic barbs. The female has smaller horns.

name: Nidorina
description: The female has a gentle temperament. It emits ultrasonic cries that have the power to befuddle foes.

name: Nidoqueen
description: The body is covered by stiff, needle-like scales. If it becomes excited, the needles bristle outwards.

name: Nidoran-m
description: Its large ears are flapped like wings when it is listening to distant sounds. It extends toxic barbs when angered.

name: Nidorino
description: It is easily angered. By swinging its well-developed horn wildly, it can even punch through diamond.

name: Nidoking
description: It is recognized by its rock-hard hide and its extended horn. Be careful with the horn as it contains venom.

name: Clefairy
description: Its adorable appearance makes it popular as a pet. However, it is rare and difficult to find.

name: Clefable
description: It has an acute sense of hearing. It can easily hear a pin being dropped nearly 1,100 yards away.

name: Vulpix
description: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

name: Ninetales
description: It has nine long tails and fur that gleams gold. It is said to live for 1,000 years.

name: Jigglypuff
description: It captivates foes with its huge, round eyes, then lulls them to sleep by singing a soothing melody.

name: Wigglytuff
description: Wigglytuff’s body is very flexible. By inhaling deeply, this Pokémon can inflate itself seemingly without end. Once inflated, Wigglytuff bounces along lightly like a balloon.

name: Zubat
description: It has no eyes. Instead, it relies on its ultrasonic cries for echo location to flit about in darkness.

name: Golbat
description: It clamps down on its prey with needle-sharp fangs and drains over 10 ounces of blood in one gulp.

name: Oddish
description: Its scientific name is “Oddium Wanderus.” At night, it is said to walk nearly 1,000 feet on its two roots.

name: Gloom
description: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

name: Vileplume
description: Its petals are the largest in the world. It fiendishly scatters allergy-causing pollen from its petals.

name: Paras
description: Growing out of the bug’s back are mushrooms called tochukaso. The mushrooms grow with the bug host.

name: Parasect
description: It scatters toxic spores from the mushroom cap. In China, the spores are used as herbal medicine.

name: Venonat
description: Its eyes act as radar, enabling it to be active in darkness. The eyes can also shoot powerful beams.

name: Venomoth
description: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.

name: Diglett
description: It burrows through the ground at a shallow depth. It leaves raised earth in its wake, making it easy to spot.

name: Dugtrio
description: In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction.

name: Meowth
description: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

name: Persian
description: A Persian’s six bold whiskers sense air movements to determine what is in its vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.

name: Psyduck
description: When its headache intensifies, it starts using strange powers. However, it has no recollection of its powers, so it always looks befuddled and bewildered.

name: Golduck
description: A Golduck is an adept swimmer. It sometimes joins competitive swimmers in training. It uses psychic powers when its forehead shimmers with light.

name: Mankey
description: Light and agile on its feet, and ferocious in temperament. When angered, it flies into an uncontrollable frenzy.

name: Primeape
description: It is always outrageously furious. If it gives chase, it will tenaciously track the target no matter how far.

name: Growlithe
description: Very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.

name: Arcanine
description: A Pokémon that is described in Chinese legends. It is said to race at an unbelievable speed.

name: Poliwag
description: Its slick black skin is thin and damp. A part of its internal organs can be seen through the skin as a spiral pattern.

name: Poliwhirl
description: Its two legs are well developed. Even though it can live on the ground, it prefers living in water.

name: Poliwrath
description: Its highly developed muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. This Pokémon can swim back and forth across the Pacific Ocean without effort.

name: Abra
description: It sleeps for 18 hours a day. It uses a variety of extrasensory powers even while asleep.

name: Kadabra
description: It happened one morning - a boy with extrasensory powers awoke in bed transformed into Kadabra.

name: Alakazam
description: While it has strong psychic abilities and high intelligence, an Alakazam’s muscles are very weak. It uses psychic power to move its body.

name: Machop
description: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

name: Machoke
description: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.

name: Machamp
description: It is impossible to defend against punches and chops doled out by its four arms. Its fighting spirit flares up when it faces a tough opponent.

name: Bellsprout
description: Bellsprout’s thin and flexible body lets it bend and sway to avoid any attack, however strong it may be. From its mouth, this Pokémon spits a corrosive fluid that melts even iron.

name: Weepinbell
description: Weepinbell has a large hook on its rear end. At night, the Pokémon hooks on to a tree branch and goes to sleep. If it moves around in its sleep, it may wake up to find itself on the ground.

name: Victreebel
description: Lures prey into its mouth with a honeylike aroma. The helpless prey is melted with a dissolving fluid.

name: Tentacool
description: Its body is almost entirely composed of water. It ensnares its foe with its two long tentacles, then stabs with the poison stingers at their tips.

name: Tentacruel
description: It lives in complex rock formations on the ocean floor and traps prey using its 80 tentacles. Its red orbs glow when it grows excited or agitated.

name: Geodude
description: Its round form makes it easy to pick up. Some people have used them to hurl at each other in a snowball fight.

name: Graveler
description: They descend from mountains by tumbling down steep slopes. They are so brutal, they smash aside obstructing trees and massive boulders with thunderous tackles.

name: Golem
description: It is enclosed in a hard shell that is as rugged as slabs of rock. It sheds skin once a year to grow larger.

name: Ponyta
description: A Ponyta is very weak at birth. It can barely stand up. Its legs become stronger as it stumbles and falls while trying to keep up with its parent.

name: Rapidash
description: It can gallop at a top speed of 150 miles per hour. It can race as fast as a bullet train while ablaze.

name: Slowpoke
description: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.

name: Slowbro
description: Its tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can’t be used for fishing anymore. This forces it to reluctantly swim and catch prey.

name: Magnemite
description: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges Thunder Wave and so on from the units at its sides.

name: Magneton
description: A linked cluster formed of several Magnemite. It discharges powerful magnetic waves at high voltage.

name: Farfetchd
description: It always walks about with a plant stalk clamped in its beak. The stalk is used for building its nest.

name: Doduo
description: A two-headed Pokémon that was discovered as a sudden mutation. It runs at a pace of over 60 miles per hour.

name: Dodrio
description: An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.

name: Seel
description: Covered with light blue fur, its hide is thick and tough. It is active in bitter cold of minus 40 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Dewgong
description: Its body is covered with a pure white fur. The colder the weather, the more active it becomes.

name: Grimer
description: Sludge exposed to X-rays from the moon transformed into Grimer. It loves feeding on filthy things.

name: Muk
description: It prefers warm and humid habitats. In the summer time, the toxic substances in its body intensify, making Muk reek like putrid kitchen garbage.

name: Shellder
description: At night, it burrows a hole in the seafloor with its broad tongue to make a place to sleep. While asleep, it closes its shell, but leaves its tongue hanging out.

name: Cloyster
description: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.

name: Gastly
description: A being that exists as a thin gas. It can topple an Indian elephant by enveloping the prey in two seconds.

name: Haunter
description: If you get the feeling of being watched in darkness when nobody is around, Haunter is there.

name: Gengar
description: It is said to emerge from darkness to steal the lives of those who become lost in mountains.

name: Onix
description: There is a magnet in its brain that prevents an Onix from losing direction while tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes steadily rounder and smoother.

name: Drowzee
description: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it’s a sure sign that a Drowzee is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.

name: Hypno
description: It carries a pendulum-like device. There once was an incident in which it took away a child it hypnotized.

name: Krabby
description: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

name: Kingler
description: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.

name: Voltorb
description: A life-form whose identity is unknown. It is said to often Screech or suddenly use Selfdestruct.

name: Electrode
description: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of “The Bomb Ball.”

name: Exeggcute
description: This Pokémon consists of six eggs that form a closely knit cluster. The six eggs attract each other and spin around. When cracks increasingly appear on the eggs, Exeggcute is close to evolution.

name: Exeggutor
description: It is called “The Walking Tropical Rainforest.” Each of the nuts has a face and a will of its own.

name: Cubone
description: It pines for the mother it will never see again. Seeing a likeness of its mother in the full moon, it cries. The stains on the skull it wears are from its tears.

name: Marowak
description: It is small and was originally very weak. Its temperament turned ferocious when it began using bones.

name: Hitmonlee
description: The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.

name: Hitmonchan
description: The spirit of a pro boxer has infused this Pokémon. It throws punches that are faster than a bullet train.

name: Lickitung
description: Its tongue is twice the length of its body. It can be moved like an arm for grabbing food and attacking.

name: Koffing
description: Its thin, balloon-like body is inflated by horribly toxic gases. It reeks when it is nearby.

name: Weezing
description: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small Koffing twins becoming conjoined as a Weezing.

name: Rhyhorn
description: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging use of Tackle.

name: Rhydon
description: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

name: Chansey
description: It lays several eggs a day. The eggs are apparently rich in nutrients and extremely delicious.

name: Tangela
description: Blue plant vines cloak the Pokémon’s identity in a tangled mass. It entangles anything that gets close.

name: Kangaskhan
description: The female raises its offspring in a pouch on its belly. It is skilled at attacking using Comet Punch.

name: Horsea
description: It maintains balance using its tail, which is wound up like a coil. It may spray ink from its mouth.

name: Seadra
description: Its body bristles with sharp spikes. Carelessly trying to touch it could cause fainting from the spikes.

name: Goldeen
description: Its dorsal and pectoral fins are strongly developed like muscles. It can swim at a speed of five knots.

name: Seaking
description: It punches holes in boulders on stream­ beds. This is a clever innovation that prevents its eggs from being attacked or washed away by the current.

name: Staryu
description: It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light.

name: Starmie
description: This Pokémon has a geometric body. Because of its body, the locals suspect that it is an alien creature.

name: Mr. Mime
description: It is adept at conning people. It is said to be able to create walls out of thin air by miming.

name: Scyther
description: It tears and shreds prey with its wickedly sharp scythes. It very rarely spreads its wings to fly.

name: Jynx
description: It speaks using a language that sounds human. Research is under way to determine what is being said.

name: Electabuzz
description: It loves to feed on strong electricity. It occasionally appears around large power plants and so on.

name: Magmar
description: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather’s body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Pinsir
description: Its two long pincer horns are powerful. Once they grip an enemy, they won’t release until the foe is torn.

name: Tauros
description: When it is about to use Tackle, it whips its body repeatedly with its three long tails.

name: Magikarp
description: It is virtually worthless in terms of both power and speed. It is the most weak and pathetic Pokémon in the world.

name: Gyarados
description: It has an extremely aggressive nature. The Hyper Beam it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets.

name: Lapras
description: People have driven Lapras almost to the point of extinction. In the evenings, it is said to sing plaintively as it seeks what few others of its kind still remain.

name: Ditto
description: It can freely recombine its own cellular structure to transform into other life-forms.

name: Eevee
description: An extremely rare Pokémon that may evolve in a number of different ways depending on stimuli.

name: Vaporeon
description: Its body’s cellular structure is similar to the molecular composition of water. It can melt invisibly in water.

name: Jolteon
description: Its cells generate weak power that is amplified by its fur’s static electricity to drop thunderbolts. The bristling fur is made of electrically charged needles.

name: Flareon
description: It has a flame bag inside its body. After inhaling deeply, it blows out flames of nearly 3,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Porygon
description: Using the most advanced technologies, scientists finally succeeded in making the first artificial Pokémon.

name: Omanyte
description: A prehistoric Pokémon that lived in the primordial sea, it swims by twisting its 10 tentacles about.

name: Omastar
description: Its tentacles are highly developed as if they are hands and feet. As soon as it ensnares prey, it bites.

name: Kabuto
description: This Pokémon was regenerated from the fossil of an ancient creature. It protects itself with a hard shell.

name: Kabutops
description: It swims freely through water. It catches prey with its scythe-like arms and drains the victim’s fluids.

name: Aerodactyl
description: It was regenerated from a dinosaur’s genetic matter that was found in amber. It flies with high-pitched cries.

name: Snorlax
description: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

name: Articuno
description: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. With its long tail trailing behind, its flying form is magnificent.

name: Zapdos
description: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. While it is flying, it makes crackling and snapping sounds.

name: Moltres
description: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. Those seeing it are overwhelmed by its orange wings that seem to be on fire.

name: Dratini
description: Even the young can exceed 6.5 feet in length. It grows larger by repeatedly shedding skin.

name: Dragonair
description: It is said to live in seas and lakes. Even though it has no wings, it has been seen flying occasionally.

name: Dragonite
description: It can fly in spite of its big and bulky physique. It circles the globe in just 16 hours.

name: Mewtwo
description: A Pokémon whose genetic code was repeatedly recombined for research. It turned vicious as a result.

name: Mew
description: A Pokémon of South America that was thought to have been extinct. It is very intelligent and learns any move.

name: Chikorita
description: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

name: Bayleef
description: A Bayleef’s neck is ringed by curled-up leaves. Inside each leaf is a small tree shoot. The fragrance of this shoot makes people peppy.

name: Meganium
description: The fragrance of a Meganium’s flower soothes and calms emotions. In battle, it gives off more of its becalming scent to blunt the foe’s fighting spirit.

name: Cyndaquil
description: It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.

name: Quilava
description: It intimidates foes with the heat of its flames. The fire burns more strongly when it readies to fight.

name: Typhlosion
description: It attacks using blasts of fire. It creates heat shimmers with intense fire to hide itself.

name: Totodile
description: It has the habit of biting anything with its developed jaws. Even its Trainer needs to be careful.

name: Croconaw
description: Once it bites down, it won’t let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.

name: Feraligatr
description: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.

name: Sentret
description: It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy, it cries loudly to warn its kind.

name: Furret
description: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.

name: Hoothoot
description: It switches its standing foot so quickly, it can’t be seen. It cries at the same time every day.

name: Noctowl
description: If it flips its head upside down, it’s a sign that it is engaged in very complex thinking.

name: Ledyba
description: It is so timid, it can’t move if it isn’t with a swarm of others. It conveys its feelings with scent.

name: Ledian
description: It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger.

name: Spinarak
description: It sets a trap by spinning a web with thin but strong silk. It waits motionlessly for prey to arrive.

name: Ariados
description: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.

name: Crobat
description: A Pokémon that gained vastly enhanced flying performance by having its legs turn into wings.

name: Chinchou
description: It shoots positive and negative electricity between the tips of its two antennae and zaps its enemies.

name: Lanturn
description: Lanturn’s light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed “The Deep-Sea Star.”

name: Pichu
description: It plays with others by touching tails and setting off sparks. This appears to be a test of courage.

name: Cleffa
description: Many appear when the night skies are filled with shooting stars. They disappear with sunrise.

name: Igglybuff
description: It has a soft and bouncy body. Once it starts bouncing, it becomes impossible to stop.

name: Togepi
description: Its shell is said to be stuffed with happiness that it shares with kindhearted people.

name: Togetic
description: It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.

name: Natu
description: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.

name: Xatu
description: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the Sun’s movement all day.

name: Mareep
description: Its fluffy coat swells to double when static electricity builds up. Touching it can be shocking.

name: Flaaffy
description: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.

name: Ampharos
description: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the tail’s light.

name: Bellossom
description: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

name: Marill
description: The tip of its tail, which contains oil that is lighter than water, lets it swim without drowning.

name: Azumarill
description: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of living things on riverbeds.

name: Sudowoodo
description: It stands along paths pretending to be a tree. If it starts raining, it seems to disappear.

name: Politoed
description: It gathers groups of others as their leader. Its cries make POLIWAG obey.

name: Hoppip
description: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

name: Skiploom
description: It blooms when the weather warms. It floats in the sky to soak up as much sunlight as possible.

name: Jumpluff
description: Blown by seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.

name: Aipom
description: It lives atop giant trees. It wraps its tail around a branch so it won’t fall off while asleep.

name: Sunkern
description: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. A year after a cold summer, their population explodes.

name: Sunflora
description: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

name: Yanma
description: Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its head. It won’t miss prey - even those behind it.

name: Wooper
description: When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.

name: Quagsire
description: A dim-witted Pokémon. It doesn’t care if it bumps its head into boats or rocks while swimming.

name: Espeon
description: Its fur has the look and feel of velvet. The orb on its forehead glows when it uses psycho-power.

name: Umbreon
description: The light of the moon changed Eevee’s genetic structure. It lurks in darkness for prey.

name: Murkrow
description: It appears near travelers to lure them into deep forests. It is said to carry misfortune.

name: Slowking
description: Being bitten by Shellder gave it intelligence comparable to that of award-winning scientists.

name: Misdreavus
description: It gets nourishment from fear that it absorbs into its red orbs. In daytime, it sleeps in darkness.

name: Unown
description: They seem to communicate among each other telepathically. They are always found stuck on walls.

name: Wobbuffet
description: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. It is said to be proof the tail hides a secret.

name: Girafarig
description: While it sleeps, the head on its tail keeps watch. The tail doesn’t need to sleep.

name: Pineco
description: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.

name: Forretress
description: It is encased in a steel shell. Its peering eyes are all that can be seen of its mysterious innards.

name: Dunsparce
description: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.

name: Gligar
description: It sails on the winds with its limbs extended to strike from the sky. It aims for the prey’s face.

name: Steelix
description: Tempered underground under high pressure and heat, its body is harder than any metal.

name: Snubbull
description: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.

name: Granbull
description: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.

name: Qwilfish
description: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.

name: Scizor
description: It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.

name: Shuckle
description: It stores berries in its shell. The berries eventually ferment to become delicious juices.

name: Heracross
description: With powerful legs and claws, it generates enough power to hurl foes over great distances.

name: Sneasel
description: It is extremely vicious and will not stop attacking until its foe is incapable of moving.

name: Teddiursa
description: It lets honey soak into its paws so it can lick them all the time. Every set of paws tastes unique.

name: Ursaring
description: In its territory, it leaves scratches on trees that bear delicious berries or fruits.

name: Slugma
description: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn’t keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

name: Magcargo
description: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit. Flames spout from gaps in its hardened shell.

name: Swinub
description: It loves eating mushrooms that grow under dead grass. It also finds hot springs while foraging.

name: Piloswine
description: Its shaggy coat makes it unable to see. It checks surroundings with its sensitive nose instead.

name: Corsola
description: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can’t live in polluted waters.

name: Remoraid
description: It clings to Mantine to feed on the big Pokémon’s scraps. This is an adaptation to avoid foes.

name: Octillery
description: It obscures its foe’s vision by spitting a cloud of murky ink. It makes its nest among boulders.

name: Delibird
description: It carries food rolled up in its tail. It has the habit of sharing food with people lost in mountains.

name: Mantine
description: When the waves are calm, one may encounter a swarm of Mantine swimming as if they are in flight.

name: Skarmory
description: Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180mph.

name: Houndour
description: It conveys its feelings using different cries. It works in a pack to cleverly take down prey.

name: Houndoom
description: Long ago, people imagined its eerie howls to be the call of the grim reaper.

name: Kingdra
description: It lives in caves on the seafloor and creates giant whirlpools every time it moves.

name: Phanpy
description: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.

name: Donphan
description: It attacks by curling up, then rolling into its foe. It can blow apart a house in one hit.

name: Porygon2
description: With planetary development software installed, it became capable of working in space.

name: Stantler
description: Staring at its antlers creates an odd sensation as if one were being drawn into their centers.

name: Smeargle
description: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.

name: Tyrogue
description: It is famous for its eagerness to fight and always nurses injuries from challenging larger foes.

name: Hitmontop
description: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by ten.

name: Smoochum
description: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.

name: Elekid
description: It generates electricity by whirling its arms. However, it can’t store the energy it makes.

name: Magby
description: Its body temperature is around 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit. It is healthy if it is breathing yellow flames.

name: Miltank
description: It is said that kids who drink Miltank’s milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.

name: Blissey
description: This kindhearted Pokémon nurses sick Pokémon to health. It senses feelings of sadness.

name: Raikou
description: It is said to have fallen with lightning. It can fire thunderbolts from the rain clouds on its back.

name: Entei
description: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

name: Suicune
description: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.

name: Larvitar
description: A Pokémon that eats soil. Once it has eaten a large mountain, it goes to sleep so it can grow.

name: Pupitar
description: Its body is as hard as bedrock. By venting pressurized gas, it can launch itself like a rocket.

name: Tyranitar
description: If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.

name: Lugia
description: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.

name: Ho-oh
description: Its feathers are in seven colors. It is said that anyone seeing it is promised eternal happiness.

name: Celebi
description: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.

name: Treecko
description: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

name: Grovyle
description: It leaps from tree branch to tree branch quite swiftly. It shows astounding agility.

name: Sceptile
description: It agilely leaps about the jungle and uses the sharp leaves on its arms to strike its prey.

name: Torchic
description: Inside its body is a place where it keeps a small flame. Hug it! It will be as warm as a hot-water bottle.

name: Combusken
description: During a battle, the hot flame in its body increases. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

name: Blaziken
description: It can clear a 30-story building in a leap. Its fiery punches scorch its foes.

name: Mudkip
description: Its power can crush boulders. It rests by covering itself with mud at the bottom of a river.

name: Marshtomp
description: Living on muddy ground that provides poor footing has made its legs sturdy.

name: Swampert
description: Its arms are hard as rock. With one swing, it can break a boulder into pieces.

name: Poochyena
description: It chases its prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it turns tail if the prey strikes back.

name: Mightyena
description: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.

name: Zigzagoon
description: It gets interested in everything, which is why it zigs and zags. It is good at finding items.

name: Linoone
description: When running in a straight line, it can easily top 60 miles an hour. It has a tough time with curved roads.

name: Wurmple
description: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by raising up the spikes on its rear.

name: Silcoon
description: Having wrapped silk around the branches of a tree, it quiescently awaits evolution.

name: Beautifly
description: Vibrantly patterned wings are its prominent feature. It sucks sweet flower nectar with its long mouth.

name: Cascoon
description: It endures attacks with patience, because the more pain before evolution, the sturdier it becomes.

name: Dustox
description: It scatters its fine dust all over when it is attacked. It is a nocturnal Pokémon.

name: Lotad
description: Its leaf grew too large for it to live on land. That is how it began to live floating in the water.

name: Lombre
description: It is nocturnal and becomes active at nightfall. It feeds on aquatic mosses that grow in the riverbed.

name: Ludicolo
description: If it hears festive music, it begins moving in rhythm in order to amplify its power.

name: Seedot
description: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.

name: Nuzleaf
description: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

name: Shiftry
description: It lives quietly in the deep forest. It is said to create chilly winter winds with the fans it holds.

name: Taillow
description: When it gets cold, they migrate, flying over 180 miles a day. It hunts for tasty prey.

name: Swellow
description: It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.

name: Wingull
description: It soars on updrafts without flapping its wings. It makes a nest on sheer cliffs at the sea’s edge.

name: Pelipper
description: It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small Pokémon and eggs to safety in its bill.

name: Ralts
description: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people’s emotions.

name: Kirlia
description: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

name: Gardevoir
description: It unleashes psychokinetic energy at full power when protecting a Trainer it has bonded closely with.

name: Surskit
description: It secretes a thick, sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.

name: Masquerain
description: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction - to and fro and sideways.

name: Shroomish
description: If it senses danger, it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.

name: Breloom
description: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

name: Slakoth
description: The way Slakoth lolls around makes anyone who watches it feel like doing the same.

name: Vigoroth
description: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.

name: Slaking
description: The world’s laziest Pokémon. It moves to another spot when there’s no food left within its reach.

name: Nincada
description: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.

name: Ninjask
description: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.

name: Shedinja
description: A strange Pokémon - it flies without moving its wings, has a hollow shell for a body, and does not breathe.

name: Whismur
description: If it senses danger, it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.

name: Loudred
description: It shouts loudly by inhaling air, and then uses its well-developed stomach muscles to exhale.

name: Exploud
description: Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremor - or like an earthquake has struck.

name: Makuhita
description: It toughens up by slamming into thick trees over and over. It gains a sturdy body and dauntless spirit.

name: Hariyama
description: It loves challenging others to tests of strength. It has the power to stop a train with a slap.

name: Azurill
description: Its tail is packed full of the nutrients it needs to grow.

name: Nosepass
description: If two of these meet, they cannot get too close because their noses repel each other.

name: Skitty
description: It’s adorable when it chases its own tail. It’s difficult to earn its trust.

name: Delcatty
description: It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a comfortable place in which to groom itself.

name: Sableye
description: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.

name: Mawile
description: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

name: Aron
description: When it evolves, it sheds the steel carapace that covered its whole body and develops a new one.

name: Lairon
description: It loves iron ore. Groups of them fight for territory by bashing one another with their steel bodies.

name: Aggron
description: You can tell its age by the length of its iron horns. It claims an entire mountain as its territory.

name: Meditite
description: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.

name: Medicham
description: Through daily meditation, it hones its spiritual power. It can sense what others are thinking.

name: Electrike
description: It stores electricity in its fur. It gives off sparks from all over its body in seasons when the air is dry.

name: Manectric
description: Its nest can be found where a thunderbolt hits. It is discharging electricity from its mane.

name: Plusle
description: It absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out its body to create crackling noises.

name: Minun
description: Exposure to electricity from Minun and Plusle promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.

name: Volbeat
description: It emits light from its tail to communicate. It loves the sweet aroma given off by Illumise.

name: Illumise
description: Its fragrance attracts a swarm of Volbeat, so they draw over 200 patterns in the night sky.

name: Roselia
description: Roselia that drink nutritionally rich springwater are said to reveal rare coloration when they bloom.

name: Gulpin
description: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.

name: Swalot
description: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.

name: Carvanha
description: They form packs to attack boats and rip out their hulls to sink them. They live in rivers in the jungle.

name: Sharpedo
description: It can swim at speeds of 75mph by jetting seawater through its body. It is the bandit of the sea.

name: Wailmer
description: It bounces playfully like a ball. The more seawater it swallows, the higher it bounces.

name: Wailord
description: It is the largest of all identified Pokémon. They jump as a pack to herd their prey.

name: Numel
description: The flaming magma it stores in the hump on its back is the source of its tremendous power.

name: Camerupt
description: It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.

name: Torkoal
description: You find abandoned coal mines full of them. They dig tirelessly in search of coal.

name: Spoink
description: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.

name: Grumpig
description: It can perform odd dance steps to influence foes. Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.

name: Spinda
description: The chances of two Spinda having identical spot patterns is less than one in four billion.

name: Trapinch
description: Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.

name: Vibrava
description: It vibrates its wings vigorously, creating ultrasonic waves that cause serious headaches.

name: Flygon
description: It is nicknamed “The Desert Spirit” because the flapping of its wings sounds like a woman singing.

name: Cacnea
description: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.

name: Cacturne
description: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.

name: Swablu
description: Its wings bring cottony clouds to mind. It grooms with springwater and loves to sit on heads.

name: Altaria
description: If it bonds with a person, it will gently envelop the friend with its soft wings, then hum.

name: Zangoose
description: Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a Seviper nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.

name: Seviper
description: In battle, it uses its bladed tail to counter any Zangoose. It secretes a deadly venom in its tail.

name: Lunatone
description: It was discovered at the site of a meteor strike 40 years ago. Its stare can lull its foes to sleep.

name: Solrock
description: A new Pokémon species, rumored to be from the sun. It gives off light while spinning.

name: Barboach
description: Barboach uses its whiskers to taste things just as a person uses his or her tongue to taste things.

name: Whiscash
description: It claims a large swamp to itself. If a foe comes near it, it sets off tremors by thrashing around.

name: Corphish
description: It was originally a Pokémon from afar that escaped to the wild. It can adapt to the dirtiest river.

name: Crawdaunt
description: A brutish Pokémon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.

name: Baltoy
description: It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.

name: Claydol
description: It is said that it originates from clay dolls made by an ancient civilization.

name: Lileep
description: It disguises its tentacles as flowers to attract and catch prey. It became extinct in ancient times.

name: Cradily
description: It lives in warm seas. Its heavy body weighs it down so it won’t get washed away in rough weather.

name: Anorith
description: An ancestral Pokémon that lived in the ocean. Over time, its eight feet transformed into wings.

name: Armaldo
description: Its enormous, retractable claws can cut through most anything. Its entire body is clad in sturdy plates.

name: Feebas
description: It is the shabbiest Pokémon of all. It forms in schools and lives at the bottom of rivers.

name: Milotic
description: It’s said that a glimpse of a Milotic and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you’re feeling.

name: Castform
description: This Pokémon can change its cells, taking different forms based on the temperature and humidity.

name: Kecleon
description: It changes its shading to match its surroundings so it can sneak up on prey. Only its belly patterns stay fixed.

name: Shuppet
description: It uses its horn to feed on envy and malice, or so it’s said. It’s very active at night.

name: Banette
description: This Pokémon developed from an abandoned doll that amassed a grudge. It is seen in dark alleys.

name: Duskull
description: If it finds bad children who won’t listen to their parents, it will spirit them away - or so it’s said.

name: Dusclops
description: Anyone who dares peer into its body to see its spectral ball of fire will have their spirit stolen away.

name: Tropius
description: The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It’s a highly favored tropical snack.

name: Chimecho
description: It uses the sucker on its head to hang from a tree or from eaves. It can produce seven different tones.

name: Absol
description: It has the ability to foretell natural disasters. Its life span is over a hundred years.

name: Wynaut
description: It tends to move in a pack. Individuals squash against one another to toughen their spirits.

name: Snorunt
description: It’s said that if they are seen at midnight, they’ll cause heavy snow. They eat snow and ice to survive.

name: Glalie
description: It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere. It uses this power to freeze its foes.

name: Spheal
description: It crosses the oceans by rolling itself on drifting ice. Fluffy fur keeps it warm when the temperature is below freezing.

name: Sealeo
description: It has a very sensitive nose. It touches new things with its nose to examine them.

name: Walrein
description: It shatters drift ice with its strong tusks. Its thick layer of blubber repels enemy attacks.

name: Clamperl
description: When it evolves, it makes a mysterious pearl that amplifies psychic powers when it’s held.

name: Huntail
description: It lives deep in the pitch-dark sea. It attracts prey by moving its tail in mimicry of a small animal.

name: Gorebyss
description: Its pink body becomes more vivid with the rise of water temperatures in the springtime.

name: Relicanth
description: Discovered by chance during deep-sea explorations, it has not changed since ancient times.

name: Luvdisc
description: Its heart-shaped body makes it popular. In some places, you would give a Luvdisc to someone you love.

name: Bagon
description: Its well-developed neck muscles and ironlike head can smash boulders into pieces.

name: Shelgon
description: It surrounds its body in an iron-hard shell to accumulate enough power to evolve.

name: Salamence
description: It’s uncontrollable if enraged. It flies around spouting flames and scorching fields and mountains.

name: Beldum
description: The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground’s natural magnetism, letting it float.

name: Metang
description: When two Beldum fuse together, a magnetic nervous system places their brains in union.

name: Metagross
description: It folds its four legs when flying. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.

name: Regirock
description: The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.

name: Regice
description: It is said to have slept in a glacier for thousands of years. Its body can’t be melted, even by magma.

name: Registeel
description: Its body is said to be harder than any kind of metal. A study has revealed that its body is hollow.

name: Latias
description: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.

name: Latios
description: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.

name: Kyogre
description: A mythical Pokémon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with Groudon.

name: Groudon
description: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with Kyogre.

name: Rayquaza
description: It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.

name: Jirachi
description: Generations have believed that any wish written on a note on its head will come true when it awakens.

name: Deoxys
description: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.
